67#include <openssl/ecdh.h>
68
69#include <string.h>
70
71#include <openssl/bn.h>
72#include <openssl/digest.h>
73#include <openssl/err.h>
74#include <openssl/mem.h>
75
76
77int ECDH_compute_key(void *out, size_t outlen, const EC_POINT *pub_key,
78 EC_KEY *priv_key,
79 void *(*kdf)(const void *in, size_t inlen, void *out,
80 size_t *outlen)) {
81 const BIGNUM *const priv = EC_KEY_get0_private_key(priv_key);
82 if (priv == NULL) {
83 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(ECDH, ECDH_R_NO_PRIVATE_VALUE);
84 return -1;
85 }
86
87 BN_CTX *ctx = BN_CTX_new();
88 if (ctx == NULL) {
89 return -1;
90 }
91 BN_CTX_start(ctx);
92
93 int ret = -1;
94 size_t buflen = 0;
95 uint8_t *buf = NULL;
96
97 const EC_GROUP *const group = EC_KEY_get0_group(priv_key);
98 EC_POINT *tmp = EC_POINT_new(group);
99 if (tmp == NULL) {
100 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(ECDH, ERR_R_MALLOC_FAILURE);
101 goto err;
102 }
103
104 if (!EC_POINT_mul(group, tmp, NULL, pub_key, priv, ctx)) {
105 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(ECDH, ECDH_R_POINT_ARITHMETIC_FAILURE);
106 goto err;
107 }
108
109 BIGNUM *x = BN_CTX_get(ctx);
110 if (!x) {
111 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(ECDH, ERR_R_MALLOC_FAILURE);
112 goto err;
113 }
114
115 if (!EC_POINT_get_affine_coordinates_GFp(group, tmp, x, NULL, ctx)) {
116 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(ECDH, ECDH_R_POINT_ARITHMETIC_FAILURE);
117 goto err;
118 }
119
120 buflen = (EC_GROUP_get_degree(group) + 7) / 8;
121 buf = OPENSSL_malloc(buflen);
122 if (buf == NULL) {
123 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(ECDH, ERR_R_MALLOC_FAILURE);
124 goto err;
125 }
126
127 if (!BN_bn2bin_padded(buf, buflen, x)) {
128 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(ECDH, ERR_R_INTERNAL_ERROR);
129 goto err;
130 }
131
132 if (kdf != NULL) {
133 if (kdf(buf, buflen, out, &outlen) == NULL) {
134 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(ECDH, ECDH_R_KDF_FAILED);
135 goto err;
136 }
137 } else {
138 /* no KDF, just copy as much as we can */
139 if (buflen < outlen) {
140 outlen = buflen;
141 }
142 memcpy(out, buf, outlen);
143 }
144
145 ret = outlen;
146
147err:
148 OPENSSL_free(buf);
149 EC_POINT_free(tmp);
150 BN_CTX_end(ctx);
151 BN_CTX_free(ctx);
152 return ret;
153}
